---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About"
  description="Why Life Momentum Score measures net momentum instead of streaks — and the philosophy behind delayed score reveals."
>
  <article class="container-page py-20 sm:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-5xl">
        You're better at hiding from yourself than you think.
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-body">
        You finished the week feeling productive. Three workouts, a couple of good books, early
        nights. So why does it feel like you didn't move an inch?
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 space-y-10">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Streaks tell flattering lies</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Most habit apps only count the good stuff. They hand you a row of green checkmarks and
            quietly look away from everything pulling in the other direction. It feels great. It also
            isn't true.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Life Momentum Score keeps one honest ledger instead. Good habits add. Bad habits subtract.
            The number you see is what's actually left over. Log five workouts and still land in the
            red — and finally understand why the week felt off.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Stop grading yourself by the hour</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            Check a score every day and you start gaming it — chasing the number instead of living
            your life. So you can hide it. Weekly and Monthly modes lock the score away until the
            period ends, so you log what really happened and meet the result with fresh, honest eyes.
          </p>
          <blockquote class="mt-5 border-l-2 border-hairline-strong pl-4 text-base italic text-body">
            “Delayed score reveals help reduce daily bias and encourage more honest self-reflection.”
          </blockquote>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Yours, and only yours</h2>
          <p class="mt-3 text-base leading-relaxed text-body">
            This kind of honesty only works in private. So there's no account, no login, no server —
            nothing to sign up for. Everything lives in your browser and never leaves your device.
            Close the tab, come back tomorrow, it's all still here. Just you and the truth.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 flex flex-col gap-3 sm:flex-row">
        <a href="/dashboard" class="btn btn-primary inline-flex">Start Tracking</a>
        <a href="/features" class="btn btn-secondary inline-flex">Explore features</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
